Prosper Loan Data¶

This project analyses a data set which contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

This Project gives an overview of the performance of the Bank, with general trends for Loan, its availers and the type of loans availed being looked into. Certain inter relations are also being looked into

Exploratory Data Analysis¶

# Finding Coorrelation between various variables

corr = df.corr()
ax = sb.heatmap(
    corr, 
    vmin=-1, vmax=1, center=0,
    cmap=sb.diverging_palette(20, 220, n=200),
    square=True
)
ax.set_xticklabels(
    ax.get_xticklabels(),
    rotation=45,
    horizontalalignment='right'
);

The above scatter correlation shows a few variables have a higher correlation compared to the other ones. Lets first analyse the correlation between Loan Original Amount and other variables. Let's start with plotting scatters for variables having higher correltaion which is shades of blue

Another observation from the heat map is that Borrower APR, LenderYield, Estimated EffectiveYield, Estimated Return are related variables, hence having a high degree of correlation

df_subset=  df.sample(frac=0.1, replace=True, random_state=1)


cat_markers = [[12, 'o'],
               [36, '^'],
               [60, '*']]

for cat, marker in cat_markers:
    df_cat = df_subset[df_subset['Term'] == cat]
    sb.regplot(data=df_subset, x='BorrowerAPR', y='LoanOriginalAmount', 
               x_jitter=0.05, marker=marker ,scatter_kws = {'alpha' : 1/3});


plt.legend(['12 Months','36 Months','60 Months']);

Most of the loans were given for a period of 36 and 60 months

Inferences

  1. Most of the Loans dispersed were of around 10,000
  2. Average estimated Yield was higher than the estimated Losses
  3. Most of the availers had a monthly income of 5,000 to 10,000
  4. Lonas were mostly availed for a period of 36 months
  5. Banks had the moct common prosper rating of 4 and 5 with the High Risk and AA category being the least
  6. Original Loan amount had the highest correlation with Prosper Rating, Term and then Monthly Income
  7. Least correlation of Original Loan amount was found with Estimated Loss
  8. Highest number of Loans availed for Debt consolidation
  9. But the lowest yield was obtained for Debt Consolidation
  10. High Risk loans were on the lower side for the bank
  11. Professionals were the highest availers for loans and they also had a higher Prosper Rating
  12. Speccific pattern was not visible for Loan amount and Effective yield but lower loan amount tend to have higher APR

Major Take aways from the assignment is thant

  • Lower Loan amounts had Higer BorrowerAPR which was mostly for 36 months
  • Professionals tend to receive more Loans compared to other classes
  • Professonals had a higher Prosper Rating which enabled them to do so
  • Bank has done pretty well in keeping High Risk loans limited and has also managed to have a higher Estimated Return compared to Estimated Losses
